  <span id="freeText17032204911928092591" style="display:none">Although I liked the writing style, I felt this book was a sad tale of a man who's life was going nowhere. His guilt was all that he lived for. MacLaverty is a good writer, that's not the issue. The issues is that the book was nothing more than a sad story.<br />Personal opinion, I guess.</span>
